On Mar 13, 2006, at 7:12 PM, Old Volks Home wrote:

> 16 Inch (Bosch 40 716), VW 211 955 425 E
>
> The right side end will usually NOT contact the glass due to the  
> curvature
> of the windshield.  It's a common thing (at least it was on my 69,  
> 73 and
> 77).  You could run a 15 or 14 inch blade on the right side, but  
> you will
> reduce coverage on the right side of the glass by doing so

I tried this once: it's better to go with 16" (400mm) blades on both  
sides.

BTW, there are some good deals online. I recently bought some Bosch  
Micro Edge wiper blades and there were two per box (not just insert  
refills) for $5.25.

